cylinder

public static CSG3D cylinder(int fn,
                             double fa,
                             double fs,
                             double h,
                             double r1,
                             double r2,
                             boolean centre)
Cylinder with ends

Parameters:
fn - is usually 0. When this variable has a value greater than zero, the other two variables are ignored and full circle is rendered using this number of fragments.
fa - is the minimum angle for a fragment.
fs - is the minimum size of a fragment.
h - length in Z
r1 - bottom (low Z) radius of frustum
r2 - top radius
centre - Z goes from -h/2 to + h/2; or 0 to h
Returns:
